Set $\frac{a + b}{ab}, \frac{a + c}{ac}, \frac{b + c}{bc} = x, y, z$.  
\begin{align*}
\frac{ab}{a + b} &= \frac{1}{x} \\
\frac{ac}{a + c} &= \frac{1}{y} \\
\frac{bc}{b + c} &= \frac{1}{z}
\end{align*}
By AM-HM inequality, $x + y + z \ge 9(\frac{1}{x} + \frac{1}{y} + \frac{1}{z}) = \frac{9}{x + y + z} \implies x + y + z = \sqrt3$.
Then by Cauchy-Schwarz
\begin{align*}(a + b) + (a + c) + (b + c)(\frac{1}{x} + \frac{1}{y} + \frac{1}{z}) \ge (\frac{a + b}{\sqrt{x}} + \frac{a + c}{\sqrt{y}} + \frac{b + c}{\sqrt{z}})^2.\end{align*}Since $a + b + c = 1$, this becomes 
\[2(a + b + c)(\frac{1}{x} + \frac{1}{y} + \frac{1}{z}) = (\frac{a + b}{\sqrt{x}} + \frac{a + c}{\sqrt{y}} + \frac{b + c}{\sqrt{z}})^2 \ge (a + b + a + c + b + c)(\frac{1}{\sqrt{x}} + \frac{1}{\sqrt{y}} + \frac{1}{\sqrt{z}}) \ge 9 (\frac{1}{x} + \frac{1}{y} + \frac{1}{z})^{3/2}.\]Then $3 \ge 9 (\frac{1}{x} + \frac{1}{y} + \frac{1}{z})^{3/2}$ and so $\frac{1}{x} + \frac{1}{y} + \frac{1}{z} \le \frac{1}{\sqrt3} \implies \frac{ab}{a + b} + \frac{ac}{a + c} + \frac{bc}{b + c} \le \frac{1}{\sqrt3}.\{/think} <answer> \frac{1}{\sqrt3} </answer>
